{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6151e8636c4f2b369406e0a6", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba8"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "28", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "Consider telecommunication through optical fibres. Which of the following statements is not true?", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "406p5", "text": "optical fibres can be of graded refractive index", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "27SQR", "text": "optical fibres are subjected to electro-magnetic interference from outside", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "ROKTj", "text": "optical fibres have extremely low transmission loss", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "bcIDN", "text": "optical fibres may have homogeneous core with a suitable cladding", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>Some of the characteristics of an optical fibre are as follows.<br /><br />(i) This works on the principle of total internal reflection.</p><p>(ii) It consists of core made up of glass/silica/plastic with refractive index <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>,</mo></math> which is surrounded by a glass or plastic cladding with refractive index <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>.</mo></math> The refractive index of cladding can be either changing abruptly or gradually changing (Graded index fibre).</p><p>(iii) There is a very little transmission loss through optical fibres.</p><p>(iv) There is no interference from stray electric and magnetic fields to the signals through optical fibres.</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61bb822a6a93c4900f6083d4", "61c089b857f018f3b4d37168", "6160245f5ec921be0f5aca6e", "6160245eecbc2a19170998fb", "629109ea3eeeda8325a8d9f6", "629f390a8c1be04eaa04bc1e", "6296212199d37d09c0a9daba", "629f3a8fcbeda431da39a0db", "616024609ab7a7d407c369e5", "64b937f50c5ddc56daf1bdfb", "64eb06f63118f713ecfef2a3", "66d5858da75f05ee8564f885"], "cpyqbExams": ["615f0e999476412f48314daf", "616059af0283de43c87e3e23"]}}